[% META title = '    Documentation Template Toolkit (.tt) Template' %]

<!-- Documentation page for documentation_tt_template -->
<div class="documentation-content">



<!-- Documentation page for     Documentation Template Toolkit (.tt) Template -->

[% META 
   title = "Documentation Template Toolkit (.tt) Template"
   description = "Template for creating new documentation using Template Toolkit format"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   category = "documentation"
%]

<div class="doc-page">
    <h1>Documentation Template Toolkit (.tt) Template</h1>
    
    <div class="doc-section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            This template provides the structure and format for creating new documentation files using 
            Template Toolkit (.tt) format. Use this as a starting point for all new documentation.
        </p>
    
    <div class="doc-section">
        <h2>Basic Template Structure</h2>
        <p>Copy and modify the following template for new documentation files:</p>
        
        <pre class="code-block">
[% META 
   title = "Your Document Title"
   description = "Brief description of the document"
   roles = "comma,separated,roles"  # e.g., "normal,admin,developer"
   category = "category_name"       # e.g., "user_guides", "admin_guides", etc.
%]

&lt;div class="doc-page"&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Your Document Title&lt;/h1&gt;
    
    &lt;div class="doc-section"&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;First Section Title&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;
            Your content goes here. You can use HTML formatting for:
            &lt;strong&gt;bold text&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;em&gt;italic text&lt;/em&gt;, 
            &lt;code&gt;inline code&lt;/code&gt;, etc.
        &lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;ul&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;List item one&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;List item two&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;div class="doc-section"&gt;
        &lt;h2&gt;Second Section Title&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;More content here...&lt;/p&gt;
        
        &lt;pre class="code-block"&gt;
<h1>Code block example</h1>
function example() {
    return "This is a code example";
}
        &lt;/pre&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;!-- Add more sections as needed --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
        </pre>
    
    <div class="doc-section">
        <h2>Metadata Explanation</h2>
        <p>The META block at the top of the file contains important metadata:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li><strong>title</strong>: The document title (appears in navigation and browser title)</li>
            <li><strong>description</strong>: Brief description of the document (used in listings and search results)</li>
            <li><strong>roles</strong>: Comma-separated list of roles that can access this document:
                <ul>
                    <li>normal - Regular users</li>
                    <li>editor - Content editors</li>
                    <li>admin - System administrators</li>
                    <li>developer - System developers</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>category</strong>: The category this document belongs to (must match one of the defined categories in documentation_config.json)</li>
        </ul>
    
    <div class="doc-section">
        <h2>CSS Classes</h2>
        <p>Use these CSS classes for consistent styling:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li><code>doc-page</code> - Main container for the entire document</li>
            <li><code>doc-section</code> - Container for each major section</li>
            <li><code>section-toggle</code> - For collapsible section headers</li>
            <li><code>section-content</code> - Content of collapsible sections</li>
            <li><code>code-block</code> - For code examples</li>
            <li><code>note-box</code> - For important notes or warnings</li>
            <li><code>admin-only</code> - For content visible only to admins</li>
            <li><code>developer-only</code> - For content visible only to developers</li>
        </ul>
    
    <div class="doc-section">
        <h2>Template Toolkit Features</h2>
        <p>You can use Template Toolkit directives for dynamic content:</p>
        
        <pre class="code-block">
[% IF c.check_user_roles('admin') %]
    &lt;div class="admin-only"&gt;
        This content is only visible to administrators.
    &lt;/div&gt;

[% # Include another template file %]
[% INCLUDE 'path/to/another/template.tt' %]

[% # Loop through items %]
[% FOREACH item IN items %]
    &lt;div&gt;[% item.name %]&lt;/div&gt;
        </pre>
    
    <div class="doc-section">
        <h2>Adding to Documentation System</h2>
        <p>After creating a new .tt file:</p>
        
        <ol>
            <li>Save it in the appropriate directory under <code>/Documentation/</code></li>
            <li>Add the file key to the appropriate category in <code>documentation_config.json</code></li>
            <li>Add the file path to the <code>default_paths</code> section in <code>documentation_config.json</code></li>
        </ol>
        
        <p>Example addition to documentation_config.json:</p>
        
        <pre class="code-block">
"categories": {
  "your_category": {
    "pages": ["existing_page_1", "existing_page_2", "your_new_page"]
  }
},
"default_paths": {
  "your_new_page": "Documentation/path/to/your_new_page.tt"
}
        </pre>

</div>
